## TEST DATA STRUCTURE

**Required Fields:**
- Adviser: Selected from available dropdown options
- Title: Mr, Mrs, Ms, Dr, etc. (Select2 dropdown)
- Forename: Generated or specified text
- Surname: Generated or specified text  
- Date of Birth: Valid date in dd/MM/yyyy format (age 18-80)
- Source of Enquiry: Selected from available options

**Optional Fields:**
- Known As: Alternative name or nickname
- Gender: Male/Female selection
- Marital Status: Single/Married/Divorced/Widowed
- Active Plan: Selected from available plans
- NI Number: UK format (AB123456C)
- Specific Source: Additional source details
- Email Address: Valid email format
- Home Phone: Valid phone number
- Mobile Phone: Valid phone number

**Generated Data Examples:**
```javascript
{
  forename: "TestForename123",
  surname: "TestSurname456", 
  email: "testforename123.testsurname456@example.com",
  dob: "15/03/1990", // dd/MM/yyyy format
  phone: "01234567890"
}
```

---

## AUTOMATION IMPLEMENTATION REFERENCE

**Key Methods from [`RetailClientCreationSteps.ts`](projects/gateway-ui/steps/gateway/RetailClientCreationSteps.ts):**
- `executeNavigateToAddClient()` - Navigation to client creation page
- `verifyClientPage()` - Page verification (URL and title)
- `createClient()` - Complete client creation workflow
- `completeRetailClientForm()` - Form completion with data
- `selectAdviser()`, `selectTitle()`, `selectSourceOfEnquiry()` - Select2 dropdown handling
- `fillForename()`, `fillSurname()` - Required field population
- `fillOptionalContactFields()` - Optional field handling
- `selectDOB()` - Date picker interaction
- Alert handling via [`AlertService`](projects/gateway-ui/steps/components/AlertService.ts)
- Data persistence via [`DataStore`](framework/src/utils/DataStore.ts)

**Page Elements from [`ClientCreationPageLocators.ts`](projects/gateway-ui/pages/gatewayElementLocators/ClientCreationPageLocators.ts):**
- Select2 triggers and rendered fields for Adviser, Title, Source of Enquiry
- Global Select2 options locator
- Form field locators for all input types

---

**Test Execution Notes:**
- All tests should be executed in a clean test environment
- Each test should start from the Gateway UI login page
- Client creation should be verified through both UI and data persistence
- Optional field tests can be combined or executed separately
- Error scenario tests may require specific environment configuration